{
  "openapi": "3.1.0",
  "info": {
    "title": "Webhook Event Handler API",
    "description": "\n## Webhook Integration API\n\nBidirectional webhook event processing service that synchronises **knowledge\narticles**, **case data**, and **usage analytics** between eGain and\nSalesforce Service Cloud.\n\n---\n\n### Integration Flows\n\n| # | Endpoint | Body `event` | Direction | Downstream |\n|---|----------|--------------|-----------|------------|\n| 1 | `POST /webhooks/article-published` | `article.published` | eGain → Salesforce | Salesforce `Knowledge__kav` sObject |\n| 2 | `POST /webhooks/case-closed` | `case.closed` | Salesforce → eGain | Content Gap API |\n| 3 | `POST /webhooks/article-viewed` | `article.viewed` | eGain → eGain Analytics | Analytics API / Kafka |\n\n---\n\n### Authentication\n\nEvery inbound webhook **must** include two headers:\n\n| Header | Format |\n|--------|--------|\n| `X-Signature` | `sha256=<64-char hex digest>` |\n| `X-Timestamp` | Unix epoch seconds (±5 min tolerance) |\n\n**Signing algorithm**\n```\nsigning_payload = f\"{X-Timestamp}.{raw_request_body}\"\nsignature       = HMAC-SHA256(shared_secret, signing_payload)\nheader_value    = \"sha256=\" + signature.hex()\n```\n\n---\n\n",
    "contact": {
      "name": "Nazneen Ansari",
      "email": "nazneen.ansari379@gmail.com"
    },
    "version": "1.0.0"
  },
  "servers": [
    {
      "url": "http://localhost:8000",
      "description": "Local development"
    },
    {
      "url": "https://integrations.egain.com/webhooks/v1",
      "description": "Production"
    }
  ],
  "paths": {
    "/webhooks/article-published": {
      "post": {
        "tags": [
          "Webhooks - Knowledge Articles"
        ],
        "summary": "Receive article-published event",
        "description": "Called by the **eGain CMS** whenever a knowledge article is published or updated.\nThe service transforms the payload and enqueues a push to **Salesforce Knowledge**\n(`Knowledge__kav` sObject).\n\nRequest body must include `\"event\": \"article.published\"`, `tenantId` (eGain tenant),\nand `appId` (the application triggering the webhook).\n\n**Processing flow:**\n1. eGain publishes article → fires this webhook\n2. HMAC-SHA256 signature is verified\n3. System validates the request body\n4. Event is enqueued → `202 Accepted` returned immediately\n5. Worker transforms the article and calls Salesforce Knowledge API",
        "operationId": "receive_article_published_webhooks_article_published_post",
        "parameters": [
          {
            "name": "X-Signature",
            "in": "header",
            "required": true,
            "schema": {
              "type": "string",
              "description": "sha256=<hex-digest> of `{timestamp}.{raw_body}`",
              "examples": [
                "sha256=4b1f3c8a9e2d7f0b6a3e5c8d1f4a7b2e9c6d0a3f7e1b4c8d2f5a9e0b3c6d1f4"
              ],
              "title": "X-Signature"
            },
            "description": "sha256=<hex-digest> of `{timestamp}.{raw_body}`"
          },
          {
            "name": "X-Timestamp",
            "in": "header",
            "required": true,
            "schema": {
              "type": "string",
              "description": "Unix epoch seconds at time of signing.",
              "examples": [
                "1717243200"
              ],
              "title": "X-Timestamp"
            },
            "description": "Unix epoch seconds at time of signing."
          }
        ],
        "requestBody": {
          "required": true,
          "content": {
            "application/json": {
              "schema": {
                "$ref": "#/components/schemas/ArticlePublishedWebhook"
              }
            }
          }
        },
        "responses": {
          "202": {
            "description": "Event accepted and queued",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/AcceptedResponse"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "401": {
            "description": "Missing or invalid HMAC signature",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/UnauthorizedError"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "403": {
            "description": "Forbidden – tenant not authorised for this operation",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/ForbiddenError"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "500": {
            "description": "Internal server error",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/InternalServerError"
                }
              }
            }
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "/webhooks/case-closed": {
      "post": {
        "tags": [
          "Webhooks - Cases"
        ],
        "summary": "Receive case-closed event",
        "description": "Called by **Salesforce** (Outbound Message or Platform Event) when a support case\nis closed. The service analyses whether the case was resolved with existing\nknowledge articles, computes a **content-gap**, and records a gap entry\nin eGain.\n\nRequest body must include `\"event\": \"case.closed\"`, `tenantId` (eGain tenant),\nand `appId` (the application triggering the webhook).\n\n**Processing flow:**\n1. Salesforce closes case → fires this webhook\n2. HMAC-SHA256 signature verified\n3. Event enqueued → `202 Accepted` returned\n4. Worker takes the data and stores it in a database for scheduled batch processing for content-gap analysis.",
        "operationId": "receive_case_closed_webhooks_case_closed_post",
        "parameters": [
          {
            "name": "X-Signature",
            "in": "header",
            "required": true,
            "schema": {
              "type": "string",
              "description": "sha256=<hex-digest> of `{timestamp}.{raw_body}`",
              "examples": [
                "sha256=4b1f3c8a9e2d7f0b6a3e5c8d1f4a7b2e9c6d0a3f7e1b4c8d2f5a9e0b3c6d1f4"
              ],
              "title": "X-Signature"
            },
            "description": "sha256=<hex-digest> of `{timestamp}.{raw_body}`"
          },
          {
            "name": "X-Timestamp",
            "in": "header",
            "required": true,
            "schema": {
              "type": "string",
              "description": "Unix epoch seconds at time of signing.",
              "examples": [
                "1717243200"
              ],
              "title": "X-Timestamp"
            },
            "description": "Unix epoch seconds at time of signing."
          }
        ],
        "requestBody": {
          "required": true,
          "content": {
            "application/json": {
              "schema": {
                "$ref": "#/components/schemas/CaseClosedWebhook"
              }
            }
          }
        },
        "responses": {
          "202": {
            "description": "Event accepted and queued",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/AcceptedResponse"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "401": {
            "description": "Missing or invalid HMAC signature",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/UnauthorizedError"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "403": {
            "description": "Forbidden – tenant not authorised for this operation",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/ForbiddenError"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "500": {
            "description": "Internal server error",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/InternalServerError"
                }
              }
            }
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "/webhooks/article-viewed": {
      "post": {
        "tags": [
          "Webhooks - Analytics"
        ],
        "summary": "Receive article-viewed analytics event",
        "description": "Called by the **eGain portal** on every article page view. Events are streamed\nto the **eGain Analytics API** (or Kafka/Kinesis in high-volume deployments).\n\nRequest body must include `\"event\": \"article.viewed\"`, `tenantId` (eGain tenant),\nand `appId` (the application triggering the webhook).\n\nThis is a **high-throughput** endpoint — expect bursts of hundreds of events\nper second during peak support hours.\n\n**Processing flow:**\n1. eGain fires view event in real time\n2. Signature verified, body validated\n3. Event enqueued → `202 Accepted` returned\n4. Worker batches and forwards to `POST /api/v1/analytics/events`\n5. Analytics pipeline updates article usage metrics in eGain",
        "operationId": "receive_article_viewed_webhooks_article_viewed_post",
        "parameters": [
          {
            "name": "X-Signature",
            "in": "header",
            "required": true,
            "schema": {
              "type": "string",
              "description": "sha256=<hex-digest> of `{timestamp}.{raw_body}`",
              "examples": [
                "sha256=4b1f3c8a9e2d7f0b6a3e5c8d1f4a7b2e9c6d0a3f7e1b4c8d2f5a9e0b3c6d1f4"
              ],
              "title": "X-Signature"
            },
            "description": "sha256=<hex-digest> of `{timestamp}.{raw_body}`"
          },
          {
            "name": "X-Timestamp",
            "in": "header",
            "required": true,
            "schema": {
              "type": "string",
              "description": "Unix epoch seconds at time of signing.",
              "examples": [
                "1717243200"
              ],
              "title": "X-Timestamp"
            },
            "description": "Unix epoch seconds at time of signing."
          }
        ],
        "requestBody": {
          "required": true,
          "content": {
            "application/json": {
              "schema": {
                "$ref": "#/components/schemas/ArticleViewedWebhook"
              }
            }
          }
        },
        "responses": {
          "202": {
            "description": "Analytics event accepted and queued",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/AcceptedResponse"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "401": {
            "description": "Missing or invalid HMAC signature",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/UnauthorizedError"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "403": {
            "description": "Forbidden – tenant not authorised for this operation",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/ForbiddenError"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "500": {
            "description": "Internal server error",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/InternalServerError"
                }
              }
            }
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "/admin/dlq": {
      "get": {
        "tags": [
          "Admin - DLQ"
        ],
        "summary": "List all events in the Dead Letter Queue",
        "description": "Returns a paginated list of events that exhausted all retry attempts.\nUse `POST /admin/dlq/{event_id}/replay` to re-enqueue any entry.",
        "operationId": "list_dlq_admin_dlq_get",
        "responses": {
          "200": {
            "description": "Successful Response",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/DLQListResponse"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "401": {
            "description": "Missing or invalid authentication credentials",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/UnauthorizedError"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "403": {
            "description": "Forbidden – insufficient permissions to access the DLQ",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/ForbiddenError"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "500": {
            "description": "Internal server error",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/InternalServerError"
                }
              }
            }
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "/admin/dlq/{event_id}/replay": {
      "post": {
        "tags": [
          "Admin - DLQ"
        ],
        "summary": "Replay a dead-letter event",
        "description": "Re-enqueues a DLQ event for reprocessing. The original DLQ entry is removed\nand a **new event** (new UUID) is created. The new event's `meta` includes\n`replayed_from` and `replayed_at` for traceability.",
        "operationId": "replay_dlq_event_admin_dlq__event_id__replay_post",
        "parameters": [
          {
            "name": "event_id",
            "in": "path",
            "required": true,
            "schema": {
              "type": "string",
              "format": "uuid",
              "title": "Event Id"
            }
          }
        ],
        "responses": {
          "202": {
            "description": "Successful Response",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/ReplayResponse"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "401": {
            "description": "Missing or invalid authentication credentials",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/UnauthorizedError"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "403": {
            "description": "Forbidden – insufficient permissions to replay DLQ events",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/ForbiddenError"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "404": {
            "description": "Event not found in DLQ",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/ErrorResponse"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "500": {
            "description": "Internal server error",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/InternalServerError"
                }
              }
            }
          }
        }
      }
    },
